text: Noah Mascoll-Gomes (born 27 May 1999) is an Antigua and Barbuda competitive swimmer. He competed at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, in the men's 200 metre freestyle. He finished 44th in the heats and did not advance to the semifinals. He was the flag bearer for Antigua and Barbuda in the closing ceremony. ==References== Category:1999 births Category:Living people Category:Antigua and Barbuda male swimmers Category:Olympic swimmers of Antigua and Barbuda Category:Swimmers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Swimmers at the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Pan American Games competitors for Antigua and Barbuda Category:Swimmers at the 2015 Pan American Games Category:Male freestyle swimmers
